THE GAME
--------

  'Whippo' is a Workbench game that is based on the familiar
'sliding-tiles' puzzles. The idea is to move tiles containing
diagonal bars so the number of bars are put in an increasing or
decreasing number from top to bottom. Of course, their colours
must match in each column.

  Playing the game is simply a matter of sliding tiles: you move
tiles horizontally by clicking on any tile located at the left or
right half of the game board, all tiles located on the same row
will move in the direction according to the position you clicked
on. A tile located at the right or left edge of the board will go
to the opposite side of the board. However, if the clicked tile is
located over or under the empty space, that tile will move up or
down towards the empty space.

  Try to solve the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

